# State Layer Conventions

`pilot/state/` is Pilot's only working memory. Whether you edit by hand or via
a Tool, the rules below apply.

## Forbidden actions

- ❌ `cat`/`head`/`tail` the full `tuning_state.yaml` into context.
- ❌ Drop the entire `candidate_pool.yaml` / `plan_graph.yaml` into the Worker
  prompt.
- ❌ Carry raw Snapshot / DiagnosisReport payloads across stages.

## Correct usage

| Goal | Command / pattern |
|------|------------------|
| Read the current stage pointers | `python -m pilot.tools.state summary` — returns < 500-token YAML |
| Read a single PlanGraph node | `python -m pilot.tools.state plan_graph.node --id <plan_id>` |
| Read the selected CandidatePool entries | `python -m pilot.tools.state candidate_pool.selected` |
| Hand a full artifact to a Worker | Pass `ref: state/round_3/candidate_pool.yaml`; the Worker reads it itself |
| Promote a champion | `python -m pilot.tools.state set_champion --id <plan_id>` |

## Checkpoint protocol

At every stage exit:

```bash
python -m pilot.tools.state checkpoint \
  --session $SESSION_ID \
  --stage $STAGE \
  --round $ROUND
```

Produces:
- `pilot/state/checkpoints/r$ROUND/tuning_state.yaml`
- `pilot/state/checkpoints/r$ROUND/plan_graph.yaml` (if changed)
- `pilot/state/checkpoints/r$ROUND/candidate_pool.yaml` (if changed)

## Resume protocol

When a new session starts:

```bash
python -m pilot.tools.state resume \
  --session $SESSION_ID
```

Returns the latest checkpoint's `summary`; continue directly from
`current_stage` — do not redo completed stages.

## Handoff protocol (Cursor-specific)

Cursor has no resident process, so a handoff is "this session exits cleanly
+ the next session resumes from the breakpoint".

Trigger conditions:
- Orchestrator context > 50% window → handoff is **recommended**.
- > 75% window → handoff is **mandatory**.

```bash
python -m pilot.tools.state handoff \
  --session $SESSION_ID \
  --reason "context_pressure" \
  --hint "$PENDING_DECISION"
```

Writes to `pilot/state/checkpoints/handoff/<session_id>.yaml`. **Tell the user
to start the next Cursor session with the same session_id**; `state.resume()`
will pick up the handoff automatically.

## gitignore

The entire `pilot/state/` directory belongs in `.gitignore`. Do not commit it.
